From Helen Trillian Rose Subject Duo slowdown problems I'm a system and network One of my users has a Duo specifications below that has been having slowdown Leaving the Duo on for several hours causes it to slow down It can take seconds to change During this time it is completely If he reboots the problem goes away For a while It seems the system is getting itself into a wedged He's re installed System and rebuilt the Neither of these have It's possible that it's network related he uses Eudora which checks his email every minutes over Ethernet He hasn't checked to see if this problem occurs while undocked he's docked most of the time Little to no non Apple inits I don't want to start yanking the rest unless I know that might really be the He hasn't tried zapping the PRAM I have advised him to do that Anyone who has ideas I'd love to hear about I'd call Apple but I've found they're best to call during the week it's Sunday evening Powerbook Duo RAM card from Tech Works to replace non self refreshing Is using System Enabler Express Modem including latest software Has been to Apple Dealer for Keyboard Helen Trillian Rose Kapor Enterprises email for EFF Info Electronic Frontier Foundation Flames to Systems and Networks Administration